{{Infobox martial artist|name=Andrey Lipchanskiy|nickname=Hulk|sherdog=388755|nationality=[[Russia|Russian]]|birth_date={{birth date and age|1984|03|22}}|height={{height|ft=5|in=7}}|weight={{convert|135|lb|kg st|abbr=on}}|birth_place=[[Magadan]], [[Russia]]|mma_win=4|mma_loss=0|mmakowins=2|style=[[grappling]], [[judo]], [[box]]|team=Golden Team|years_active=2018|image=Andrey Lipchanskiy.jpg}}
'''Lipchanskiy Andrey'''' (born 22 March 1984) hereditary Kazak Donskoy - [[Russian fighter aces|Russian]] [[ mixed martial artist]] representative of the [[lightweight]] category. Has been performing professionally since 2018. He played for the Golden Team, was a member of the Rod national team until 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Andrey Lipchanskiy {{!}} MMA Fighter Page|url=https://www.tapology.com/fightcenter/fighters/303328-andrey-lipchanskiy|access-date=2021-10-30|website=Tapology|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Третье место в соревнованиях по грепплингу занял спортсмен школы «Динамо-Ивантеевка»|url=http://inivanteevka.ru/novosti/sport/02-03-2015-15-38-24-trete-mesto-v-sorevnovaniyakh-po-grepplingu-zanyal|access-date=2021-10-30|website=Пульс Ивантеевки}}</ref>

== Biography ==
Lipchansky was born on 22 March 1984 in [[Magadan]].

'''Army'''

On June 24, 2002, he was drafted into the army from the city [[Pushkin]] of the Ministry of Defense. The first 6 months he served at 145 OSB in the Seim settlement of the Nizhny Novgorod region, up to the rank of junior sergeant.

After in [[ Nizhny Novgorod]] in 84 ORB in the RDR. There he performed in army hand-to-hand combat in 2003, took first place in the tournament.

He rose to the rank of senior sergeant. And at the end of the service already the rank of foreman.

'''Sports career'''

Russian mixed style fighter (MMA), representative of the lightest weight category. Amateur boxing career since 2001. Amateur judo career since 2004. Since 2015 wrestling sport Grappling. He has been performing at the professional level in MMA since 2018, he is known for his participation in the tournaments of the "Strelka" fighting organization. He played for the “Golden Team” team, since 2018 he was a member of the Rod club's national team. He is also a titled amateur athlete: Master of Sports in Boxing CCM in judo CCM grappling MO bronze medalist in grappling Professional record of a fighter 3 wins 0 losses.

