{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2021}} {{short description|German footballer and manager}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Enrico Maaßen | image = | image_size = | fullname = Enrico Maaßen | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1984|3|10|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Wismar]], East Germany | currentclub = [[Borussia Dortmund II]] (manager) | height = 1.78m | position = [[Midfielder]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = Grevesmühlener FC | youthyears2 = | youthclubs2 = SKV Bobitz | youthyears3 = | youthclubs3 = [[FC Anker Wismar]] | years1 = 2003–2005 | clubs1 = [[FC Anker Wismar]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | years2 = 2005–2006 | clubs2 = [[FC Hansa Rostock II|Hansa Rostock II]] | caps2 = 10 | goals2 = 0 | years3 = 2006–2007 | clubs3 = [[Greifswalder SV 04|Greifswalder SV]] | caps3 = | goals3 = | years4 = 2007–2009 | clubs4 = [[SC Verl]] | caps4 = 22 | goals4 = 0 | years5 = 2009–2011 | clubs5 = [[Goslarer SC 08|Goslarer SC]] | caps5 = 56 | goals5 = 5 | years6 = 2011–2014 | clubs6 = [[SV Drochtersen/Assel]] | caps6 = | goals6 = | manageryears1 = 2014–2018 | managerclubs1 = [[SV Drochtersen/Assel]] | manageryears2 = 2018–2020 | managerclubs2 = [[SV Rödinghausen]] | manageryears3 = 2020– | managerclubs3 = [[Borussia Dortmund II]] }} '''Enrico Maaßen''' (born 10 March 1984) is a German professional [[Manager (association football)|football manager]] and former [[Football player|player]] who is the manager of [[Borussia Dortmund II]].
==Playing career== A [[FC Anker Wismar]] youth graduate, Maaßen only played amateur football during his entire career. He subsequently represented [[FC Hansa Rostock II]], [[Greifswalder SV 04]], [[SC Verl]], [[Goslarer SC 08]] and [[SV Drochtersen/Assel]], retiring with the latter in 2014 at the age of 30, after suffering a serious [[knee]] injury.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spox.com/de/sport/fussball/regionalliga/2006/Artikel/enrico-maassen-das-ist-der-neue-trainer-beim-bvb-ii-borussia-dortmund-skibbe-ftr.html|title=Borussia Dortmund – Enrico Maaßen: Das ist der neue Trainer beim BVB II|trans-title=Borussia Dortmund – Enrico Maaßen: This is the new coach at ''BVB'' II|publisher=Spox|language=de|date=15 June 2020|accessdate=1 November 2021}}</ref>
==Managerial career== Immediately after retiring, Maaßen was named manager of his last club SV Drochtersen/Assel. On 7 March 2018, after nearly four years in charge, his club confirmed that he would leave the post at the end of the season,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sv-drochtersen-assel.com/2018/03/07/enrico-maassen-hoert-bei-d-a-als-trainer-auf/|title=Enrico Maaßen Hört Bei D/A Als Trainer Auf|trans-title=Enrico Maaßen is leaving ''D/A''{{'}}s manager role|publisher=SV Drochtersen/Assel|language=de|date=7 March 2018|accessdate=1 November 2021}}</ref> and he was confirmed as manager of [[SV Rödinghausen]] for the 2018–19 campaign seven days later.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sv-drochtersen-assel.com/2018/03/14/enrico-maassen-wird-trainer-beim-sv-roedinghausen/|title=Enrico Maaßen Wird Trainer Beim SV Rödinghausen|trans-title=Enrico Maaßen becomes a manager at SV Rödinghausen|publisher=SV Drochtersen/Assel|language=de|date=14 March 2018|accessdate=1 November 2021}}</ref>
On 12 June 2020, Maaßen was appointed manager of [[Borussia Dortmund]]'s [[Borussia Dortmund II|reserve team]], replacing [[Mike Tullberg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bvb.de/News/Uebersicht/Enrico-Maassen-wird-neuer-Cheftrainer-der-U23|title=Enrico Maaßen wird neuer Cheftrainer der U23|trans-title=Enrico Maaßen is the new head coach of the U23|publisher=Borussia Dortmund|language=de|date=12 June 2020|accessdate=1 November 2021}}</ref> He renewed his contract until 2024 on 21 May of the following year,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bvb.de/eng/News/Overview/Enrico-Maassen-signs-contract-extension|title=Enrico Maaßen signs contract extension|publisher=Borussia Dortmund|date=21 May 2021|accessdate=1 November 2021}}</ref> and achieved promotion to the [[3. Liga]] with the side on 7 June 2021 after a 2–1 win over [[Wuppertaler SV]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bvb.de/eng/News/Overview/A-brilliant-feeling-Interview-with-Enrico-Maassen|title="A brilliant feeling" – Interview with Enrico Maaßen|publisher=Borussia Dortmund|date=7 June 2021|accessdate=1 November 2021}}</ref>
