{{Infobox military person | name = Vasily Mikhailyov | native_name = Василий Павлович Михалёв | image = Василий Павлович Михалёв.jpg | birth_date = 20 March 1917 | death_date = 10 December 2006 | birth_place = [[Ulan-Ude|Verkhneudinsk]] | death_place = [[Samara]], [[Russia]] | allegiance = {{flagicon|Soviet Union}} [[Soviet Union]] | branch = {{flagicon image|Flag of the Soviet Air Force.svg}} [[Soviet Air Forces|Soviet Air Force]] | serviceyears = | rank = Colonel | unit = | commands = | battles = [[World War II]] | awards = [[Hero of the Soviet Union]] }}
'''Vasily Pavlovich Mikhalyov''' ({{lang-ru|Василий Павлович Михалёв}}; 20 March 1917 — 10 December 2006) was a Soviet fighter pilot during [[World War II]]. Awarded the title [[Hero of the Soviet Union]] on 1 July 1944 for his initial victories, he totaled over 20 solo aerial victories including an aerial ramming during the war, although the exact tally is subject to some dispute.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Bykov|first=Mikhail|title=Все асы Сталина. 1936–1953|publisher=Yauza|year=2014|isbn=978-5-9955-0712-3|location=Moscow|pages=800-801|trans-title=Aces of Stalin. 1936–1953|oclc=879321002}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Kargapoltsev|first=Sergey|title=Михалёв Василий Павлович|url=https://warheroes.ru/hero/hero.asp?Hero_id=7384|url-status=live|access-date=2021-11-01|website=warheroes.ru|language=ru}}</ref>
